{
  "stem": "4753.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But then you heard the mother screaming and beating the child, trying to make them alive again.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And the sick people died.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Finally, after four and a half days' ride, we arrived somewhere.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the train stopped.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the door opened up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember when the door opened up, I felt such happiness, such a relief.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But that took just one second and every feeling gone because I looked into a pitch dark emptiness full of tortures, two SS men standing by the railroad car and two striped uniformed so-called [INAUDIBLE], whom I didn't know who these guys were.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Later, I learned they were Jewish young men chosen by the SS men to do the most horrible things on Earth to do to their own people.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were telling us to jump from the train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We couldn't even get up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And finally, the people-- we, 2,000 people-- got off from the train, except the dead, naturally.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They told us, [INAUDIBLE], we should leave the packages.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Everything will follow us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when we all came off from the train, the noise was deafening.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "People were screaming and crying, calling each other.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I remember so clearly how I holded onto my mother and my little brother and my father and the other aunt, making a ring together, desperately trying to keep together.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the loudspeaker came on and told us to separate, the men should come form a group.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And women and children should form another group.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[CRYING] And then my little brother unfortunately turned to me and asked me, where do I belong-- to the men or to the women?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because in the Jewish religion, when you reach age 13, you become a bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What does that mean?",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
